rComments: simidchieva is quite unclear during lectures and a little unorganized but she is a VERY sweet person! helps if you go to her. lot of memorization needed for this course (tests are hard) and can only do well if willing to put in a lot of studying/memorizing before test. tests are quite detailed! TAs were awesome!

Not cool...Prof is not clear, doesn't know how to use notes or powerpoint, very unorganized and can't put a sentence together. Our TA was not on top of things.  Assignments are hard. For a 2nd year course its very difficult.

a difficult class with tough terminology but simidchieva is a fair prof. expect only to do well if you are ready to put time & effort into this class. its no bird course. she will go out of her way to help you if you ask for it.
easy marker.... i don't know how anyone could think otherwise...

The amount of material and the difficulty of the material covered does not corrospond with the level of the class (this is supposed to be a second year class and fourth year students are having difficulty). Testing questions are often unclear and the marking is therefore sparadic (there has to be a problem when that many students agree).
